<text id="04-procedure" title="Unit Testing — Procedure" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="medium">
  <summary>Step-by-step procedure for applying unit-testing.</summary>

    <section title="Step 1: Pick one behaviour">
      <p>Input: Spec / ticket</p>
      <p>Action: Identify one observable input → output.</p>
      <p>Output: Behaviour stated.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2: Arrange">
      <p>Input: Behaviour picked</p>
      <p>Action: Set up minimal fixtures, fakes, inputs.</p>
      <p>Output: Setup block.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3: Act">
      <p>Input: Setup ready</p>
      <p>Action: Call the unit under test (one line).</p>
      <p>Output: Result captured.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4: Assert">
      <p>Input: Result captured</p>
      <p>Action: One observable assertion.</p>
      <p>Output: Test complete.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5: Review">
      <p>Input: Test runs</p>
      <p>Action: Verify isolation, idempotence, name.</p>
      <p>Output: Test merged.</p>
    </section>
</text>
